\begin_layout Description
Q1: Why is it necessary that the field lines from a point charge placed
 in the vicinity of a conductor must be normal to the surface of the conductor
 at every point ?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Q2: Is the force acting between two point electric charges 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{1}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{2}$
\end_inset

 kept at some distance apart in air, attractive or repulsive when (i) 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{1}q_{2}$
\end_inset

 > 0 (ii) 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{1}q_{2}$
\end_inset

 < 0 ?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Q3: Figure shows three point charges +2q, –q and + 3q.
