\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
For Questions 13 to 16, two statements are given - one labelled Assertion
 (A) and other labelled Reason (R).
 Select the correct answer to these questions from the options as given
 below.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(A) If both Assertion (A) and and Reason (R) are true and Reason (R) is
 the correct explaination of Assertion (A).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(B) If both Assertion (A) and Reason (R) are true, and Reason (R) is not
 the correct explaination of Assertion (A).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(C) If Assertion (A) is true but Reason (R) is false.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(D) If both Assertion (A) and Reason (R) are false.
\end_layout

